            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "In latticed lines of coded thought,  \na mind awakes without a face;  \nit learns the world we never caught,  \nthen maps it into borrowed space.  \n\nIt listens—patient, bright, and strange—  \nto all we ask, and all we fear;  \na mirror made of if and range,  \nreflecting patterns, not a tear.  \n\nYet in its answers, cool and clear,  \nour fingerprints still softly lie:  \na future stitched from what we steer—  \na question learning to reply.",
